SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1081
By Oliver
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Dr. Christiane Buggs,
executive director of Nashville PENCIL.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should salute those citizens who, through their
extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community leaders of whom we can all
be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Dr. Christiane Buggs, who serves as the
executive director of Nashville PENCIL (Public Education Needs Community Involvement and
Leadership), a Nashville nonprofit organization that links community resources for Metropolitan
Nashville Public Schools (MNPS) to help young people achieve academic success and prepare
for life; and
WHEREAS, a respected professional with proven successes in building partner and
donor relationships, Dr. Christiane Buggs is a fifth-generation Nashvillian and has engaged with
public education in Nashville throughout her life an MNPS alumna, former MNPS teacher, past
MNPS school board chair, and current MNPS parent; and
WHEREAS, a former middle school math teacher for MNPS, Dr. Buggs successfully ran
for the MNPS Board of Education in 2016 and was re-elected to a second term in 2020, quickly
becoming its chair as the school district continued to navigate the aftermath of the March
tornadoes and the COVID-19 pandemic; and
WHEREAS, in her role at Nashville PENCIL, Dr. Buggs's strong passion for and
commitment to the students of Metro Nashville Public Schools guides her in leading PENCIL to
support MNPS by recruiting business partners and serving as a teacher resource center,
ensuring that all of our students have equitable access to resources and opportunities; and
SJR1081
016912
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Dr. Buggs epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are characteristic of a
true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Dr. Christiane Buggs for
her dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that, on March 30, 2026, National Pencil Day, we honor
and commend Dr. Christiane Buggs, executive director of Nashville PENCIL, for her
tremendous service to the children of Nashville and the State of Tennessee and extend to her
our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
